          <p>Venus is the second planet from the Sun and the hottest planet in our solar system. Often called Earth's twin due to similar size and composition, Venus is anything but hospitable—with crushing atmospheric pressure, temperatures hot enough to melt lead, clouds of sulfuric acid, and a backwards rotation. Despite its hellish conditions, Venus may have once harbored oceans and habitable conditions, making it a fascinating subject for planetary science.</p>
